The paper focuses on human-centric applications and their impact on wireless networks, which suggests a strong connection to the computer science sub-category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel learning method for modeling human delay perception, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also explicitly models the limitations of the human brain, indicating a connection to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Furthermore, the paper discusses virtual reality and immersive gaming, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a brain-aware resource management algorithm based on Lyapunov optimization, which falls under the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
